headline: The 'giant' retail winners as US consumers become more choiceful
summary: Storch Advisors CEO Jerry Storch disagrees with the notion that American consumers are spending more "choicefully" as major retailers like Walmart (WMT), TJX Companies (TJX), and Amazon (AMZN) continue to thrive, further illustrated by recent earnings results. Storch is the former CEO of Toys R Us and Hudson's Bay. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Catalysts.
